Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* role with *Affirm*. I bring over three years of professional experience designing and launching backend systems and APIs at scale, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the distributed systems design and API-at-scale depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and launched a backend API layer serving 1,000+ platform endpoints — applying distributed systems patterns including input validation, safe tool-call execution, and multi-component orchestration to power reliable, scalable automated customer workflows. I also architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph with Python, enabling scalable task dispatch and fault-tolerant coordination across independent backend service components. To keep these systems production-ready, I optimized API routing and agent concurrency to maximize KV-cache hit rate, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and lowering operational costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic backend service in Python backed by PostgreSQL and Redis, exposing a well-tested, extensible API for file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO. I also built a backend search and ranking system using LangChain RAG with a PostgreSQL vector store — enabling natural-language search and intelligent ranking of documentation — and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to orchestrate long-running data import jobs, ensuring the reliability and scalability of async processing pipelines. Together, these roles have prepared me to own high-leverage technical initiatives, contribute meaningfully to Affirm's Home and Search Experience team, and strike the right balance of speed and quality while protecting systems from downtime.

My research experience at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab reinforced the engineering rigor and collaborative communication skills your team values. I managed distributed ML training pipelines on Pace University's HPC cluster using Python, PyTorch, CUDA, and LORA — coordinating data preparation, training runs, and inference optimization with vLLM — while also leading technical workshops for 50+ students on GPU programming and building AI Agents. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex multi-component systems clearly and accessibly, directly mirroring the collaborative and proactive communication style Affirm values in its engineers.

I have always been passionate about building honest financial products that improve people's lives and empowering consumers to spend and save responsibly. I would love to discuss how my experience building scalable backend APIs and distributed systems can contribute to Affirm's search and discovery mission. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration — I look forward to connecting!

